### Type Guards

**USE**: `guards.ts` from `@utils/guards`

**Available functions:**
- `isTruthy<T>(item)` - Type guard for truthy values
- `isNonNullish<T>(item)` - Type guard for non-null/undefined values

**DO NOT**: Create custom type guards for these common cases

```typescript
import { isTruthy, isNonNullish } from "@utils/guards";

const items = [1, 0, "", null, undefined, "test"];
const truthy = items.filter(isTruthy); // [1, "test"]
const nonNull = items.filter(isNonNullish); // [1, 0, "", "test"]
```

