### Miscellaneous Utilities

**USE**: `misc.ts` from `@utils/misc`

**Available functions:**
- `classes(...classes)` - Join class names (filters falsy values)
- `sleep(ms)` - Promise that resolves after delay
- `isObject(obj)` - Check if value is a plain object (not array/null)
- `isObjectEmpty(obj)` - Check if object has no own properties
- `parseUrl(urlString)` - Parse URL safely (returns null on error)
- `checkIntersecting(el)` - Check if element is on screen
- `identity<T>(value)` - Identity function
- `isPluginDev(id)` - Check if user is Vencord plugin dev
- `shouldShowContributorBadge(id)` - Check if should show badge
- `isEquicordPluginDev(id)` - Check if user is Equicord plugin dev
- `shouldShowEquicordContributorBadge(id)` - Check if should show Equicord badge
- `isAnyPluginDev(id)` - Check if user is any plugin dev
- `pluralise(amount, singular, plural?)` - Pluralize words
- `interpolateIfDefined(strings, ...args)` - Template literal that returns "" if any arg is null/undefined
- `tryOrElse<T>(func, fallback)` - Try function, return fallback on error
- `isEquicordGuild(id, isGuildId?)` - Check if channel/guild is Equicord guild
- `isSupportChannel(channelId)` - Check if channel is support channel
- `isEquicordSupport(userId)` - Check if user is Equicord support

**DO NOT**: Recreate these common utility functions

```typescript
import { classes, sleep, isObject, parseUrl, pluralise } from "@utils/misc";

const className = classes("base", condition && "active", "item"); // "base active item"
await sleep(1000); // Wait 1 second
if (isObject(value)) { /* ... */ }
const url = parseUrl("https://example.com"); // URL | null
const text = pluralise(5, "item"); // "5 items"
```

